  <section class="section" id="links">
    <h2 class="section__title">Links</h2>
    <p class="section__text">Textual links should be underlined and contain arrows, to draw attention to a single call-to-action. Use these links for links, not buttons. The only time when textual links should not be underlined or have an arrow is if they appear in the context of a block quote.</p>

    <p class="section__text">Because the link underline is created using the background-image and gradient method, you must change the color of the <code>text-shadow</code> if you have a background color that is different than the default color of <code>#fcfcfc</code>.</p>


